Here is your **testsmells.org 19-smell academic catalog** audit for `UserRepositoryIntegrationTests.cs` (MSTest, `[TestCategory("Integration")]`).

---

## Summary Dashboard

| Severity | Smell Count | Affected Tests |
|----------|-------------|----------------|
| **High** | 3           | 3              |
| **Medium** | 1         | 1              |
| Low      | 0           | 0              |
| **Total** | **4**      | **4**          |

---

## Findings by Severity

### ❌ HIGH — Smell 3: Sleepy Test

**Test:** `NotifyOnInsert_SendsEventAfterDelay` (line 87)
**Integration calibration:** Sleepy Test remains **High** even for integration tests — `Thread.Sleep` is never the right synchronization mechanism.

```csharp
Thread.Sleep(3000); // ← blocks 3 s with no guarantee the event is ready
```

**Fix — poll with a timeout:**

```csharp
var timeout = TimeSpan.FromSeconds(5);
var sw = Stopwatch.StartNew();
while (sw.Elapsed < timeout)
{
    if (_repository.WasNotificationSent(user.Id))
        break;
    await Task.Delay(50);
}
Assert.IsTrue(_repository.WasNotificationSent(user.Id),
    "Notification was not sent within the expected timeframe.");
```

**Risk if unfixed:** Non-deterministic failures in CI; adds 3 s to every suite run; hides real race conditions.

---

### ❌ HIGH — Smell 1: Conditional Test Logic

**Test:** `GetUser_ReturnsCorrectType` (lines 101-108)

```csharp
if (loaded is PremiumUser premium)
{
    Assert.IsTrue(premium.DiscountRate > 0);
}
else
{
    Assert.AreEqual("Eve", loaded!.Name);
}
```

Only one branch runs per execution — the other path is **never tested**.

**Fix — split into two deterministic tests:**

```csharp
[TestMethod]
public void GetUser_WhenStandard_ReturnsCorrectName()
{
    _repository.Insert(new User("eve@example.com", "Eve"));
    var loaded = _repository.GetByEmail("eve@example.com");

    Assert.IsNotNull(loaded);
    Assert.AreEqual("Eve", loaded.Name);
}

[TestMethod]
public void GetUser_WhenPremium_HasPositiveDiscount()
{
    _repository.Insert(new PremiumUser("eve@example.com", "Eve", discountRate: 0.1m));
    var loaded = (PremiumUser)_repository.GetByEmail("eve@example.com")!;

    Assert.IsTrue(loaded.DiscountRate > 0);
}
```

**Risk if unfixed:** One branch is silently untested — a bug in the untested path will never surface.

---

### ❌ HIGH — Smell 4: Assertion-Free Test (Unknown Test)

**Test:** `BulkInsert_RunsWithoutErrors` (lines 113-119)

```csharp
public void BulkInsert_RunsWithoutErrors()
{
    for (int i = 0; i < 100; i++)
        _repository.Insert(new User($"bulk{i}@example.com", $"Bulk User {i}"));
    // ← no assertion
}
```

The `_RunsWithoutErrors` naming suggests a *DoesNotThrow* intent — acknowledged. However, MSTest reports this as passing even if inserts silently corrupt data.

**Fix — assert the postcondition:**

```csharp
[TestMethod]
public void BulkInsert_PersistsAllRecords()
{
    for (int i = 0; i < 100; i++)
        _repository.Insert(new User($"bulk{i}@example.com", $"Bulk User {i}"));

    Assert.AreEqual(100, _repository.ListAll().Count,
        "All 100 bulk-inserted users should be persisted.");
}
```

**Risk if unfixed:** False confidence — coverage metric goes up, but nothing is actually verified.

---

### ⚠️ MEDIUM — Assertion Roulette (Extended Catalog)

**Test:** `InsertUser_PersistsToDatabase` (lines 35-39)

```csharp
Assert.IsNotNull(loaded);
Assert.AreEqual("Alice", loaded.Name);
Assert.AreEqual("alice@example.com", loaded.Email);
Assert.IsTrue(loaded.Id > 0);
```

Four assertions, zero explanation messages. When one fails, the MSTest runner says *"Assert.AreEqual failed. Expected:<Alice>. Actual:<null>"* — but without context about **which property** was wrong or **why** it matters.

**Fix — add diagnostic messages:**

```csharp
Assert.IsNotNull(loaded, "User should be retrievable after insert.");
Assert.AreEqual("Alice", loaded.Name, "Name should round-trip unchanged.");
Assert.AreEqual("alice@example.com", loaded.Email, "Email should round-trip unchanged.");
Assert.IsTrue(loaded.Id > 0, "Database should assign a positive ID on insert.");
```

**Risk if unfixed:** Extra triage time on CI failures; especially painful in parallel test runs.

---

## Smells Scanned — No Findings (15 of 19 clean ✅)

| Smell | Status | Notes |
|-------|--------|-------|
| Mystery Guest | ✅ Clean | In-memory SQLite — no external resources (integration-calibrated) |
| Eager Test | ✅ Clean | No test calls 4+ distinct production methods |
| Magic Number Test | ✅ Clean | `3` and `10` in assertions are contextually obvious (items just added) |
| Sensitive Equality | ✅ Clean | No `ToString()` in assertions |
| Exception Handling | ✅ Clean | No `try`/`catch` in test methods |
| General Fixture | ✅ Clean | `_connection` and `_repository` are used by every test |
| Ignored/Disabled Test | ✅ Clean | No skipped tests |
| Duplicate Assert | ✅ Clean | No duplicated assertions |
| Lazy Test | ✅ Clean | `Insert` is called as setup, not as the primary action under test |
| Constructor Initialization | ✅ Clean | Proper `[TestInitialize]` usage |
| Default Test | ✅ Clean | Class is meaningfully named |
| Redundant Print | ✅ Clean | No print/log statements |
| Redundant Assertion | ✅ Clean | No tautological assertions |
| Resource Optimism | ✅ Clean | In-memory DB, no assumed files |
| Empty Test | ✅ Clean | All methods contain executable statements |

---

## Prioritized Remediation Plan

| Priority | Smell | Test | Effort | Why First |
|----------|-------|------|--------|-----------|
| 1 | Conditional Test Logic | `GetUser_ReturnsCorrectType` | ~10 min | Eliminates a **hidden testing gap** — one branch is untested today |
| 2 | Assertion-Free Test | `BulkInsert_RunsWithoutErrors` | ~2 min | One-line fix turns a false-pass into a real check |
| 3 | Sleepy Test | `NotifyOnInsert_SendsEventAfterDelay` | ~10 min | Removes 3 s of dead wait and a flakiness source |
| 4 | Assertion Roulette | `InsertUser_PersistsToDatabase` | ~3 min | Adds diagnostic messages to speed up future triage |

**Bottom line:** 4 of 8 tests have smells, but 3 of the 4 are quick fixes. The suite's setup/teardown, fixture design, and naming are solid. Address the three High-severity items and this is a clean suite.
